OL,3,C87-year-old with dementia left on care
OL,4,Chome floor for hour after fall
OL,6,FCharlotte Baines, prosecuting, said it
OL,7,Fwas well known the man was prone to
OL,8,Ffalls and should not be moved without
OL,9,Fhelp from the ambulance service,
OL,10,Funless he was able to stand on his own.
OL,12,FThe pensioner was sitting in a chair
OL,13,Fin a room off a hallway when he tried
OL,14,Fto stand, using a nearby walking frame
OL,15,Fto help himself up.
OL,17,F"He eventually got to his feet but
OL,18,Flost his balance and fell on to the
OL,19,Ffloor," Miss Baines said. "He began to
OL,20,Fcry out."
