OL,3,C87-year-old with dementia left on care
OL,4,Chome floor for hour after fall
OL,6,FMiss Baines said the distressed man
OL,7,Fcould be heard saying "Please, please."
OL,9,FA couple of minutes later Brown came
OL,10,Finto the hallway and asked the
OL,11,Fpensioner what he was doing and why he
OL,12,Fwas crawling around.
OL,14,FMiss Baines said: "She told him that
OL,15,Fhe needed to sit in a chair in the
OL,16,Fhallway. She told him that she cannot
OL,17,Flift him on her own and remarked that
OL,18,Fthere was not enough staff."
OL,20,FBrown told another resident: "He's
OL,21,Fokay because he's moving around."
