OL,3,C87-year-old with dementia left on care
OL,4,Chome floor for hour after fall
OL,6,F"He understood his situation and I
OL,7,Fimagine it was embarrassing and even
OL,8,Fhumiliating for an adult to be left
OL,9,Fthat way. Other residents saw him and
OL,10,Fsaw you ignoring him.
OL,12,F"You left one of your patients on the
OL,13,Ffloor. He was left unaided for an
OL,14,Fhour. You inflicted no injury. You
OL,15,Fsimply failed to care for a man who
OL,16,Fhad fallen."
OL,18,FBoth defendants were given community
OL,19,Forders. Brown was given 110 hours'
OL,20,Funpaid work. Khaengraeng was given 80
OL,21,Fhours' unpaid work.
